This levy obligation enables the German financial administration to verify compliance with the revenue limit for small business owners.
In addition, the relevant FA may match the annual VAT statement with the corresponding declarations for direct taxes and with the financial statements of the company concerned.
In the Czech Republic, the financial administration can only verify the amount of turnover on the basis of the income tax return issued.
In contrast to the current regulations in the Czech Republic, German taxpayers are obliged to file the VAT pre-registration.
The introduction of the obligation to file the tax return in the Czech Republic would increase the efficiency of the Czech financial administration.
