VAT risk management
Risk management in the Czech Republic
In the Czech Republic, several organisational units at different levels of financial management are involved in risk management in the area of VAT.
Within the Czech Ministry of Finance, the following organisational units are responsible for risk management and the fight against VAT fraud:
The Risk Tax Policy and Economic Administration Department or its Risk Management Unit deals with identifying potential risk areas for tax revenues and evaluates trends in these risks in domestic and domestic and national Intra-Community trade.
At the national level, this body coordinates the requirements for the criterion "Credibility of VAT returns" and uses the MIAS data to detect possible tax evasion in the context of intra-Community deliveries and acquisitions.
Based on data on the trade balance of the Czech Republic, it evaluates high-risk goods, conceptually prepares risk management in the area of VAT and works in this area with the relevant EC institutions and the others. Member States together.
The Department for International Administrative Assistance in the area of VAT provides, among other things, the exchange of information, participates in the creation and maintenance of a relevant information database, evaluates the data available in the MIAS system, provides Public relations and is responsible for other forms of intergovernmental administrative assistance within the meaning of Council Regulation (EC) 1798/2003.
