Tax investigators are held by the financial directorates. Its tasks include finding taxpayers and industries that are risky in terms of the frequency of tax evasion (e.g. internet transactions, gold, pharmaceutical industry), finding unregistered taxpayers (e.g. in the Sectors Internet services, employment services, electronic and print media, etc.), the investigation of interconnectedness in chain fraud cases and the information of local tax authorities.
Special test units have been set up in 12 selected subjects.
